choices.text:
by walking – we just did it!

1.7km from the grams place there was a lovely hill that I got to climb every day and take gorgeous pictures of the coves around Monaco…the top of the hill was so lush and green, compared to what life in Monaco must be choose – dry and hot 90% of the year.

Even on the walk to the grocery store it didn’t rain, so the lush didn’t have anything to do with the rain…it was just really green and beautiful up there! Thanks brother and father in law for showing us around for a weekend!

That is my mom, she is so great, she has been coming with me shopping leaving the 2 younger kids at home with dad. She has also been taking me with START buses and the FINtrans express, since I don’t like having to stick to the schedule for them. She has been so gracious to drive my sister in law and I to Fontainbleau on Wednesday and Paris on Thursday this week.

It was a 4.5 hour drive to Fontainbleau (just a village for day tourists), but so well worth the trip. I got very nostalgic on this trip for my days when I lived in and around the Fontainbleau villages. This town and surroundings was where I spent the first ever days that I was alone in a foreign country as an exchange student. I had German 1 host family not speaking German, that rocks!! But I have such wonderful memories there
